reviews.text: The architecture of the building it is situated in is interesting, and there are some paintings by famous Romanian artists, but I expected to see more paintings, maybe some by internationally painters, which was not the case.
One of the remarkable buildings, represents an important era which defines the history of the city. Unfortunately it is in deplorable condition.
A place to visit for Art lovers. One of the best spot around the center. It’s a must to see!
Very nice.Fine building.Easy accessible
Romanian artists with rare paintings.it is a very good way to understand the Romanian art evolution. The guide is recommended.was well informed and pleasant.

Nothing is related to Pazhassi Raja. It’s just a honour to him.

Museum is at east hill which was one of administrative block of British rule in Malabar. Well maintained and guide at museum help us to know the history of all artefacts displayed. No photos allowed. Best for one day trip especially school children.
A nice sport for relaxation and also a heritage place. Alots of things to study and a wonderful experience will get from there. Need to go there

Some interesting artefacts here. But the low budget allocation is obvious. They have done the best they can to maintain the museum, but the lack of resources is a big let down. And the artefacts themselves are nothing to write home about. A few clay pots and weapons catch your attention. 

Visit, if only if you are in the area.

This is located near to Calicut staff over here are not cooperative. you have to keep the exact change in your hand otherwise they will not I love you inside if you don't have change there is no option to enter inside.. card swiping also not available...
Quite informative; came across articles og bygone era. Engrossing. The guide ther, English speaking, trained was quite helpful. Time usefully spent..

Loved all of the accompanying dishes so you can create your own flavor combos. We got there just in time, around 6:30 before the mobs of people started to arrive around 7. The service was terrific, fast, warm smiles and the staff all had a collective effort. Be sure to say hi to the owner/host, he was the nicest guy and you can tell he took pride in his restaurant. We’ll definitely be back, but next time we’re trying the bbq table :) 

Also - be sure to get the chicken dumplings to start

It was good but I wouldn't say that it was stellar and I would come back. The food was average and the place is definitely historic. They need to up their game given there are many other fantastic korean good food options in Austin now. The place is a little hard to find as it is tucked away near a small Chinese Zen garden. The service was okay and took a while. We requested a few things but didn't get it on time. We had to ask the waiter multiple times. The interior was a little dim and bland. The tofu soup was really great though, not so sure about the cold noodles. It is worth a one time try but I can't fully recommend it as a too option, there are a lot other better ones.
We got Korean BBQ combo and everything was amazing! Great atmosphere, very helpful staff. Loved it!!
Have been coming here for ten years plus. Never a bad experience! Great atmosphere, and wonderful people.

Always great. They have cleaned, updated and renovated the place. They also performed a menu update after the previous owner, who was also the sushi chef, retired. No more sushi is a bummer. Also, my favorite dish consisting of stir fried baby octopus is gone. I was initially sad that my favorite dish was gone but it forced me to try something new and I was not let down! They were busy for lunch and all the diners seemed content. I will always come back.

My girlfriend and I visited Fujiyama on a Saturday night. And they were packed!  it is a beautiful restaurant with a great ambience.  We were seated rather quickly. It took the waitress a little while to come and take our order. After waiting for our order for over an hour we asked the waitress if we can get it to go. It was brought out minutes later.  If the wait wasn’t so long I’d give this place five stars.

The sushi on the other hand was absolutely amazing!  We ordered five separate rolls and each one was better than the last.

This place is definitely a five-star restaurant but when they get packed on the weekends it is crazy.

We will definitely be going back to Fujiyama in the future but next time we’ll get our order to go.

Great place for a special lunch.  Food is always amazing, staff is friendly and helpful.  Some visits may have been better then others but that has nothing to do with the food.  I really love the ambiance of the place.. you get a great feeling when you walk in and it all makes for s great dining experience.  😋

I went here for my grandmother's birthday and we had the best night! The staff is so kind and I believe the manager personally sang happy birthday to her. I recommend anyone to come here if they have the time.

Fujiyama is a fun place to go with a crowd. For the past several years my niece has selected this hibachi restaurant as her go to place for a birthday party that includes family and close friends. The chef does his best to entertain guests with a little cooking show. Although I can't help but think he is laughing at us peasants as he tosses food in the air to catch in your mouth. The food is okay. Veggies, rice and shrimp are always good. Meat usually gets to dry and is not tasty. I guess that's why you get lots of sauce. The place is a bit loud so can be a challenge to hear even the person next to you. But not bad for a once a year gathering.
japanese food and the setting here is great. I like it here, great food & service. Fast, efficient, and courteous service. The bill won't break you.
Nice but very simple. Good tour with a deacon!
Nice looking cathedral.

Although it's clearly free for people to walk the grounds of this church, I was approached and escorted to a ticket office by a staff member. The office asked for 200birr! I told them I didn't want to go inside the cathedral and they said I still had to pay or I had to leave. The place had dozens of people walking the grounds who I highly doubt paid 200birr. Still I left the grounds. Even after exiting I was reprimanded by a guard for standing on the street near the cathedral. I'm used to getting foreigner prices,  but this is ridiculous.
Must visit in Addis. Better with guide for more interesting stories
Amazing design and painted windows, great hospitality

If you are looking for somewhere inexpensive to have some lunch then come here as you have plenty to choose from. At this centre you cam buy almost anything from pork to chicken and everything in between and it will just cost under S$10 For a nice meal.
We have pork and duck meat with a pork soup and it was delicious. If you want to try something different then go for the black skin chicken. For drinks you can get anything from water to tea or coffee.
I had so much fun that hippies are so cool I smoke some of the best weed for the best price

A great space and part of Berkeley's story, student accommodation not sure? A refuge and a place of reflection for Berkeley siders, keep People's Park as it is, a moving story and inportant history that should be preserved and improved.

Peoples Park is a precious green space. I play live acoustic music at Peoples Park whenever I get a chance, guitar songs, jazz, funk, folk, rock, samba, bossa nova, percussion... I have old friends there and did community gardening there for five years, growing 13 foot tall corn and green beans, and all kinds of stuff. The trees and plants there are good old friends too. I've heard lots of great bands on the Free Speech Stage, summer concerts, the Berkeley World Music series, drum jams, dancing. Its very interesting, I've learned a lot there, talking to people, about history, people, culture, plants, gardening.

I have always loved this old park.
Sad it is always under attack and it is purposely kept decrepit by the University to justify building on it.
Guess everyone will use Williard Park should the unelected have their way.

A little off the beaten track but worth the visit. Good combination of everything from tanks to history and aircraft. As you enter the main building you can see cannons and guns from the earlier times and on your right more modern equipment. Main building gives the early years which is impressive, sometimes with a English translation which makes things easier. The heating was on at a very toasty 24 deg a little warm this time of year. In the back of the building there is a courtyard full of varying equipment which sadly is decaying over time. There are three other buildings one on transport at the back which was locked at the time. One on aviation, and another on arms. Very impressive. Overall worth a visit for anyone with a military interest.

The museum is OK, reasonable amount of exhibits and plenty of old military vehicles in the courtyard. What lets it down are the lack of explanations relating to exhibits or anything else. No map provided to help patrons find particular exhibits/areas of interest, staff not unfriendly, nor enthusiastic or overly helpful. One certainly didn't meet anyone who had any passion for sharing history with patrons which has been commonplace at nearly every other museum one has visited in my lifetime. In comparison to other museums it's pretty poor but if you have time to kill and are in the area it's worth a visit, I wouldn't advise anyone to go out of their way to visit unless you are a huge fan of real life tanks and other military vehicles as seeing them up close in the flesh is really the only selling point of the place.

Great museum, but be aware there are not a lot of explanations inside. The museum assumes a good knowledge of the Romanian history.  The decaying military vehicles in the courtyard are very interesting to explore.

Great place to visit in Bucharest, hosting an impressive collection of objects from the Romanian military history. It covers all the historical times from the bronze age to contemporary present day. Make sure you also go to the courtyard behind the main building where for real size military equipments like tanks, guns, trucks & even aircrafts. 

As well, there are 3 other pavilions situated in the back of the main building that host collections of military transport vehicles & chariots, military uniforms & weapons. 

Prices range from 5 lei (children & students) to 20 lei (adults). Just make sure you have cash with you because you can't pay by card at the entrance.

A great museum where you can learn a lot about Romania's history from a military point of view. It features from crude stone tools to rockets used until the 1990's. Small scale fortification and castle models. A lot of maps and uniforms. And from small artillery guns that could be towed by horses to train fixed heavy artillery guns. Tanks, planes, armoured carriers old and relatively new.
There is a main museum, in another building a level for guns and a level for uniforms, another building for aviation related stuff and also one building.(which was closed) with parachutes and related material.

Very small museum, cool knowledgeable guides that seem to master a lot of the countrie's historic, traditional and mythological stories. In an hour you can see most part of it. There is a little shop outside of the museum where you can buy some artifacts that are also available elsewhere at lesser price.
I like this place but I would love it if it had enough traditional and local object. I think it doesn't represent enough the national heritage

I loved visiting this museum. I wish I could've taken pictures. Nevertheless, our tour guide, William Dayo, was very well versed in each of the exhibits. It was really nice to have someone with us who gave us in depth information on what we were viewing. It gave us a deeper understanding and appreciation for each of the artifacts.
It was nice. The museum has a lot to offer in cultural history and I was happy to see them opened on a Sunday.

This museum continues the tradition of equating Western African culture and history mainly with masks (sarcasm). It could almost be interchangeable with the museum's in Dakar and Bamako except they both have a second floor dedicated to textiles. 

Granted, the masks are interesting and high quality, but they are completely decontextualized with cryptic captions an little explanation tying anything together.

There is one table showing the evolution of money that was nice. 

It's one of the few times I wished there was a museum gift shop with some books. 

Weirdly they don't allow photography either, as if history should be hidden. 

Avoid the restaurant out back it is way overpriced and there are better maquis around.
Friendly staff, nice food. We had a banquet for 7 people with a pile of beers. Loads of well prepared, tasty food and reasonably priced as well.
Really nice surroundings lovely friendly staff and great food.  Brilliant value for money.  Well worth a visit.
Fantastic food and friendly service. Only place that has good aromatic crispy duck. They make some great food.
Would give zero stars if possible. Food was terrible, and the service was even worse! Avoid like the plague.
Remember that You have to pay extra money for rice. Beef was... lets say "good" and the service really nice.

It was my first time to the place, it is a bit tricky to get there are it is inside a building on the 1st floor, but once there, you will find everything well set, not that fancy. I was looking for a light vegan meal, so I went for the vegetable spring rolls and the glass noddles soup, both were very nice, it toke a bit of time to get the plates but it was hot and well served. Prices are a bit higher than expected for portions but accepted. Will go back to try out other plates.

I know it is challenging to run a resto business, especially if it serves fish, which need to be fresh and freshly cooked. Same with other dishes - be it poultry or meats or even veggies. But that is what customers look and pay for. Thai cuisine is famous for the use of freshest ingredients that are often stir fried or steamed - cooking methods that relies so much on how fresh the ingredients are. I hope Sabai Sabai continues to improve on this. I am a real fan and would encourage others to try this. Perhaps a steady flow of diners would help ensure good turnover of fresh ingredients.

A delightful place for Asian (especially Thai & Malay) cuisine tasting & experience. They offer ample variety choices of food, desserts & drinks here. The dishes are very delicious, well presented and mostly accurate with the original taste from the origin nations. Very satisfying if you’re an Asian/someone with passion for the Asian taste.

The place is very nice & comfortable to enjoy your meal. The location is exact as in the Google Maps, but the restaurant entrance can be a bit confusing to look for, do ask people around if you’re lost.
The entrance of the building complex is not that welcoming. Authentic Thai food and jasmine rice are so good. Thai beer as well as Egyptian beer served here! Friendly. Great service.

It used to be my favorite Thai place but the quality has gone down a lot lately, to the extent that I won’t be eating there again, UNLESS I hear of some major quality improvement.

The curry in all the dishes I have had lately has been very diluted: watery consistence and very limited flavor. Also the ingredients (seasoning and vegetables) have just been LESS in terms of diversity and quantity.

I had a duck curry, which came out super fatty and the sauce was dominated by a strong odor that was on the fishy side. If anyone with a basic sense of smell and no culinary experience had smelled THAT, they would have flushed it down the toilet, not offered it to customers.

Sabai SabIai used to be my foolproof recommendation to friends in Zamalek and the surrounding areas, it will go back to being so if you significantly improve quality AND consistency.

So good luck.

Went there for a Saturday Buffet date with wife and we had a great evening. The place has nicely set up the ambiance for a romantic dinner date  They serve some really good  food, spread was limited but nicely curated. The desert section was my favorite as it had a lot of variety.

Not at all a great place at that price. Nothing great about ambience or food. Small place actually. Staff service is good and courteous. Less staff. You need to go hotel reception to pay your bill. No ice cream in the desert.
Food is good but limited starters in buffet. ambience was good. If you want have some privacy like closed doors environment I would suggest not to choose monsoon

A descent place to dine-in. Courteous staff and good service.

Food - we tried pizza, pasta and desserts. Pizza was very good but pasta disappointed a bit in terms of taste and quality. The raspberry cheesecake was not good but chocolate bomb was unique.
Ambience - average.
Service - very good staff.

It's been quite some time and we were craving for buffet lunch. After looking for multiple options, we found this to be better than others. This buffet was labelled as fit and healthy so we were also excited for some amazing healthy stuff. Since we reached there just when the buffet started so we thought main course items are yet to be kept. To our greatest surprise there was no main course. So the menu comprised of salads and desserts which is so weird and bizarre. The only main course option was cold burger and cold sandwich which was terrible. Except for khao suey soup and couple of salads n desserts, majority of the offerings were average to below average. The most horrific of all was papadi chaat where the ingredients were papadi and dahi, neither it was healthy nor justified to not put basic ingredients. Healthy doesn't mean non inclusion of basic items. With salads which anyways is an indispensable part of the buffet plus umpteen desserts which has nothing to do with healthiness this buffet was the worse ever experience so far. Coming to their service, it was again not even close to what we expected. The serving folks lacked basic skills in regard to everything. The only sigh of relief was the ambience which was surely in line with what we expected. Overall not suggested in any case!!!
Remember this place from more than 20 years ago. Always loved going here even as a child. Must go back!!
The ambience is great, but the food is ok, not so much level of surprise. The lunch is reasonable and recommended.
Tasty food. Ravioli must try. Very yummy. Nice ambience.
Nice Italian restaurant.  Up to the standards.
Fine dine Italian cuisine, this restaurant is over 30 years, win many awards. Romantic atmosphere in the restaurant section. The pizzaria and wine bar section more relax.

If you are looking for somewhere inexpensive to have some lunch then come here as you have plenty to choose from. At this centre you cam buy almost anything from pork to chicken and everything in between and it will just cost under S$10 For a nice meal.
We have pork and duck meat with a pork soup and it was delicious. If you want to try something different then go for the black skin chicken. For drinks you can get anything from water to tea or coffee.
I had so much fun that hippies are so cool I smoke some of the best weed for the best price

A great space and part of Berkeley's story, student accommodation not sure? A refuge and a place of reflection for Berkeley siders, keep People's Park as it is, a moving story and inportant history that should be preserved and improved.

Peoples Park is a precious green space. I play live acoustic music at Peoples Park whenever I get a chance, guitar songs, jazz, funk, folk, rock, samba, bossa nova, percussion... I have old friends there and did community gardening there for five years, growing 13 foot tall corn and green beans, and all kinds of stuff. The trees and plants there are good old friends too. I've heard lots of great bands on the Free Speech Stage, summer concerts, the Berkeley World Music series, drum jams, dancing. Its very interesting, I've learned a lot there, talking to people, about history, people, culture, plants, gardening.

I have always loved this old park.
Sad it is always under attack and it is purposely kept decrepit by the University to justify building on it.
Guess everyone will use Williard Park should the unelected have their way.
Worth seeing while at Bryce Canyon. No hiking require. Just park your car and walk 100 to 300 feet depending what parking space is available.

Been here, done that ... want more
If you have not been here ... GO HERE IMMEDIATELY .... WOW ... this place takes your breath away.

I can not go back fast enough.

To save time on all the places up here to review ... they are all 5 ... do them all and take your time and enjoy it.
Cool place. Buts not really a bridge. It's an arch
This pace was so cool. Come here to see the natural Bridge! You're really not expecting it down the canyon wall and then bam--there it is! Awesome!
Just a beautiful view with color painted constant changes. Is a must see oic you are anyplace neat.  That whole entire area Bryce Cayon included is a sight to see.

Great place. Whether you'd like a delicious coffee or a four course dinner, you'll be well served there. The Atmosphere at Frenchie's is subtle, refined and artsy because the owner is an art collector. There is a broad collection of art literature, interesting catalogues and magazines spread across the space, which is another plus.

A little bit of France in Kiev. Always here when I'm in Kiev :-) 
Breakfast very good and tasty, recommended
Wonderful little place, staff were very polite and has a really cool French jazz club vibe, loved it!
Nice place for good cuisine
Nice place. Fish solyanka was delicious.

Our regular hotel when staying in Bangkok, it has rarely disappointed us through our 10+ stays.
Staff is polite and service minded, front desk is usually quick and rooms are nice and, compared to many European hotels, quite spacious.
Big thanks to Suparp and the rest of the guys that greet us when arriving and help with our luggage. Always polite, smiling and service minded.
Breakfast restaurant is good with a huge variety of food, although I prefer to go outside for the local Bangkok taste!

The location is wonderful, right in the city center. Service is good, the staffs are quite helpful. Nice and clean, although a bit small.

Restaurants available everywhere and close to multiple malls like Siam center, Siam Paragon, MBK. The shopping mega Platinum is also just one station away, or if you don't mind the walk, there's a free walkway that takes you nearby as well.

فندق جميل وعجيب من الخدمه الي السكن في الغراف. وحتي الموظفين محترمين وطيبين وحتي الفندق قريب من المول سيام بركون 
Nice hotel! Great, convenient location. The check in staff were really friendly and helpful. I arrived early but Pump managed to find a room with no fuss and no waiting. Thank you!!
Great staff and service.  Good breakfast with variety. Close to everything.  Would stay here again.  Has a pool and a small gym.  Add pa as well.

This hotel wasn't really that nice. The only upside was its location within walking distance of shopping malls, restaurants, street sellers and markets, massages and salons. Personally won't go back as I didn't feel that comfortable there. Made use of the spa for a for massage which was pretty good.
Friendly staff, nice food. We had a banquet for 7 people with a pile of beers. Loads of well prepared, tasty food and reasonably priced as well.
Really nice surroundings lovely friendly staff and great food.  Brilliant value for money.  Well worth a visit.
Fantastic food and friendly service. Only place that has good aromatic crispy duck. They make some great food.
Would give zero stars if possible. Food was terrible, and the service was even worse! Avoid like the plague.
Remember that You have to pay extra money for rice. Beef was... lets say "good" and the service really nice.
Love this pub. Great music and reasonably priced drink. Brilliant atmosphere, especially at Christmas.
Nice old fashion pub, with good music and friends
Great Place for a Quiet pint, Lovely Guinness, Bartenders super Lovely and Nice
An amazing place to stay, the atmosphere and everything about this place is a definite place to go if traveling to Inverness, I would recommend this place first and foremost
Truly remarkable place that takes you back in time with a spectacular array of music.

As a responsible citizen every one of us should visit this place once.  It is a nice place. Fun place for kids too . It contains ruins of history. Loved it . The museum was closed though but will be open soon. Do visit! 😊😊

A nice place for kids. They will love the old trains and engines. The museum is also very well built and explained. Loved the engine simulators. Wish they have more counters to manage the ticket booking experience

Nice place to visit with kids. They have almost all the engines of Indian railways since beginning. Take the toy train ride for Rs 20 per person. It will show u almost all of the museum in 10 minutes ride. Monorail ride is also there. Easily reachable by cab

EXPLORE THE HISTORY OF INDIAN RAILWAYS AT NATIONAL RAIL MUSEUM
Discover the 163 years of rich Indian Railway’s historic heritage in the company of rare steam, diesel and electric locos, royal saloons and lots of artifacts. Interactive display will enhance the experience of visitors and make them understand how a single investment of Indian Railway helped in unification and progress of India as a nation.
Spend a day with your family and friends and enjoy joy and toy train rides, 3D virtual reality experiences, simulator rides, coupled with a sumptuous meal at newly built heritage restaurant.

A very good and enjoying place on centre of Delhi. It's very entertaining for all age personal with a full day trip. Reasonable price restaurant and very informative to the person who want to know any thing about the railway. The virtual reality show of railway and it's develop is too good.
Saturday evening dinner outside was great. Loved our waitress Anna! Great prices and great seating. Food was delish and well priced. Definitely coming back again.

Way better than I expected! Prices are decent and, despite having a smoking floor, there was no smoke smells in here at all! This was a concern of mine, but I’m glad I gave it a shot! The chicken fingers look pretty damn good, but I ended up getting some appetizers.

THE best lobster bisque!!  I could have ten bowls and I consider myself fairly broadly experienced as I adore bisque!  Great chunks of lobster, prices are SUPER reasonable and service is extremely welcoming.  We had a quick meeting in town but this was a highlight meal of our whole trip.
I got food poising here (and still want to come back) that's how delicious the Hand Dipped Corn Dogs are. However, if cigar smoke bothers you... I would ask to be seated outside.
The kitchen was closed temporarily while a piece of equipment was being repaired but my meal still came out promptly and was delicious.
Very nice staff and the food was excellent. Didn't take long to arrive and was hot and fresh. Pretty consistent ordering at Pizza Express. There is a takeaway option also if you need to dash.
Very good pizza. Perfect service. I will come back for sure ;).
Such good food! At first it looks like a fast food restaurant but the food is really good quality and tasty!
Good pizza, slow service.
Delicious food. Friendly, helpful staff.

So salty and spicy I can’t finish my overpriced meal. The “lamb” tasted old too. I am usually very forgiving about stuff like this, but not today, and they use microwaves.  Next day: I was pooping water all day and now I’m dehydrated.

First time after countless walk by’s. Honestly a bit underwhelmed by the front ( as mentioned by others the bathroom sink totally caught me off guard but at least it has somewhere to wash up 😆) clearly is labeled that everything is self serve and hey that’s not for everyone. I ordered for three to go and the dishes were great, spicy is advertised not correctly it’s on a volcanic level! The chicken was great and the lamb even better and the samosas were wonderful (as well as the accompaniments) without a doubt I will return to try different entrees ( but I won’t be dinning in). Than you Luzzat for a good experience in Rogers Park!
Cute storefront restaurant that serves great Indian food. When they say spicy, they mean spicy! Very homey feeling.

The food is tasty. Great breads. You can never be sure when they will be open. You have to order at the counter and pick up your entre at the counter, it used to be table service. Water from styrofoam cups. About half their original menu is redacted from the printed menu with opaque tape. So, yummy but not a great environment. At least it is clean.

Really high quality food in very basic surroundings. Do if you seek very good northern Indian food you will find it. But unless you take it home, you will be eating on styrofoam plates with plastic silverware. 
The adventure of going there and having the food hot and fresh is worth it at least once. 
We will return there for sure. A jewel in the rough in Jarvis in Roger's Park. I recommend it!

Great place for group, dates, solo hangout. The food was great. The drinks was great. Great selection of drinks. Prices can range from Rm10-300. Take your pic. Very enjoyable place. The band tonight was awesome! The singers was lit! Very recommend to go for a night out.

Took a while until I got a menu, staff was walking past me a lot and looking at me but not doing anything, made me feel a bit weird coming there alone. Once I was able to order it was all good. The pizza was awesome!
What can i say except this place is perfect & the service is excellent. Came here countless of times. Now let's talk about the food...yes the food...they are superb!!! 😊 worth every cent
nothing much, just good vibes good songs and etc ....

5 stars for the food, 0 star for the service. The food was extremely good and the ambience is just perfect for any occasion. We came here for my mum’s birthday celebration. However, your stuffs’ attitude was terribly bad, one of the stuffs showed unwillingness and impatience when we asked her to take photos for us. That spoiled the whole dining experience tonight. As a restaurant with reputations, you should have trained your stuffs better. We customers pay for the food as well as the service that you provide, if your stuff is unwilling to serve the customers with an open heart, then she should stay out from the service line. What’s worser than horrible food? Horrible service. I would love to come back again for the food, but you don’t deserve a second chance if your stuff’s attitude remains the same.

As silver member got free upgrade to junior suite. One of the best suites i've been to. On 11 floor with balcony to the sea and great view on the city. Breakfast is also good with big variety. Recommend.
Awesome hotel. Really clean, well laid out rooms. The staff are all friendly, professional and helpful. Breakfast is amazing and the bar serves good food throughout the day. Highly recommend!

Very good location, clean rooms, very good breakfast.. There is a cosy lobby bar with friendly staff.
Fitness room is very small and hot water gets cold sometimes..
Location wise it gets all the 5 stars. Pretty clean. Friendly staff. Decent breakfast and lovely breakfast lounge. Ideally I would want a room with a view of the Caspian.
Stayed here for 1 night new years eve. Room was comfortable and clean. Located walking distance from the mall and restaurants

Cheap and fast. Tastes cheap and fast. Not that it's bad, it's just not as good as Japanese food can get. I had high hopes. But they did a great job with getting our food out quick due to it being an hour before a show. Bento boxes look good.

In the 10+ years I've been going here, it never disappoints. Excellent staff, great food. As authentic as you're going to get in London. It would be a crime if high rents and redevelopment ever touched this joint.

Amazing service and the food was very authentic! We had free snacks and Japanese tea on arrival. I also liked that we were given our bill after we ordered so it allowed us more freedom to leave when we wanted.

Awful place!!!  If you enjoy being shouted at in front of others and overpriced food this is the place  for you. Staff are rude and abrupt with no manners!!! The food is virtually inedible, dry and tasteless!! Woman on the till openly discriminates and we felt pushed to leave due to her attitude and hostility towards us!!! Won’t be going back, can get a better quality of food and service elsewhere.
Great food and reasonably priced, always enjoy their food. Does get busy so you might have to wait a bit. Service is quick and food is not Michelin star, but very tasty.

This is a special artsy place in Bulawayo City Centre. You must visit the artist studios where you get an intimate feel of the beautiful art work while it's been made. The store there also have wonderful paintings so it's a great place  to purchase gifts.

Very difficult rating for me. Food was great. Place not very clean. A little dusting, a fan, ready waiters and easy to move chairs to allow customers to sit well would greatly improve the place. So its a place with great potential just not being managed properly.
Artwork is superb and people vibe is good during exhibition nights on Wednesday .
Real good place. Home of the limitless
It's a nice Quiet place to look at beautiful paintings and more art work
Show!

É claro que não seria algo grandioso pois o Governador Valadares é uma cidade pequena. Ademais, havia uma área não completa que parecia ser meio abandonada. No entanto, o conteúdo apresentado neste museu é muito informador sobre a cidade, verdadeiramente aprendi muito sobre a cidade do meu pai e senti mais orgulho da história da minha família. Além do mais, a arquitetura antiga preservada agrada os olhos. O atendimento também foi ótimo, as moças que trabalham lá conversavam conosco e nos ofereciam mais informações sobre o museu e a cidade. É uma pena que muitos não conhecem este museu, pois realmente vale a pena o visitar para conhecer cada vez mais a nossa história!
Uma excelente opção para conhecer a história de Governador Valadares. O acervo poderia melhorar. A planta original da cidade precisa de restauração urgente.
Me surpreendeu. Apesar do espaço ser alugado, tem muitos atrativos e retrata a história da cidade. Mais pessoas deveriam conhecer.
Relembrei de coisas que fizeram parte da minha família e da minha vida.

After eating sushi at places recommended on the web, I read about this place in a magazine. Some lady said that she goes there once a week. It sounded interesting so we decided to try it. I had CHEF’S SELECTION OF TODAY’S BEST,  the best sushi I have ever had. I know I’m repeating myself but I have been to at least two Michelin sushi places and Momoya is in my opinion better than those. I will go again.

Exceptional professionalism, incredible kitchen team, and tantalizing flavors. Balanced dishes that combine sushi with Pan Pacific flair -- you cannot, simply cannot go wrong. Do order the crispy tuna sushi, the steak as an appetizer, the crispy shrimp, and everything else :) I've been over a dozen times since it opened and while the queues have gotten longer, the staff are top notch. I've left feeling supremely grateful each time. Absolutely worth the wait and journey here. Excellent value for offerings, and the ingredients are always fresh 🏆🙏🏼  Kudos!!!
Best sushi I’ve had in nyc for a while. Great service, super lively crowd. They open the front windows when it gets warm so it’s basically outdoor seating. Truffle tuna tortilla is a MUST try

Lively Japanese restaurant with a good selection of sushi and sashimi dishes. The service was a little spotty and inconsistent, possibly due to the lunch hour rush. Customers who arrived later and sat next to us received their food quicker. Nonetheless, food was delicious and would recommend another visit.
Wow! This place is amazing! Very authentic, ingredients are high quality. Service was great. Had to wait a bit, but totally worth it!

Huge building, interesting from the architectural point of view. Museum itself has exhibitions on prehistory, a bit on stone and iron age, something on nomad tribes etc. I found the part on ethnic minorities in Kazakhstan very interesting. Museum could do with some refurbishing, it could be more interactive.

Enormous stylish building with interesting spaces to fill yet it looks like a High school end of the year science-history fair. This Museum is so badly curated !!! The information in English, French or German are whimsical. This Museum is a pale echo to the one in Nursultan (Astana).
The reward to go there is located on the 2nd floor with bits and bobs on the Soviet era spacial program and, possibly, one if the 3 Sputnik prototype... no information available!!!
The Museum shop is unbelievably lame.
Has lots of exhibits in 4 large halls. Some are more interesting than others but well worth a stop.

The building is impressive and located in a lovely park. 

The museum itself is okay, there are a few nice objects but nothing that will blow your mind. Mostly recreations rather than actual archeological artifacts. There was a very charming series of dioramas about the various ethnic groups living in Kazakhstan. 

Go if you have the time, but don’t worry about missing it, if coming here strains your itinerary.
Nice. Ticket of adults 300 tenge. For students 200 tenge and pupils 100 tenge.

Awesome food taste... The ambience was classy.... 
We went there on a working day and the corn on toast is a must try for all... 
Te
He atmosphere is electric 
The summers are the best time to hangout and The Taj is the  best place to hangout with widespread menu
The buffet is affordable and taste is mind-blowing 
Try it guys.... I'm sure you won't be disappointed....

Great vegetarian restaurant. It has Indian and Asian both cuisines. There was varieties of  North and South Indian dishes, and many varieties of dessert and the taste was awesome. I found this to be one of the finest Buffet options for Vegetarians. It is located in banjara hills opposite city centre mall. It's a well maintained restaurant with adequate parking space. If you are pure Veg Lover and you will enjoy this place. Quality of Food and service is good. This place is neat and clean With good ambience.

For all who has been frequently visiting Taj Mahal Hotel at Abids, this one is a branch of the same. Excellent food and authentic taste. Service is wonderful. Valet parking is available. Value for money.

A wonderful place to gorge on some delicious stuff, with the variety of disaster standing out. Add to this the very courteous staff and the location, you can't ask for more. However, a small suggestion. A lot of senior citizens visit this place and they should be served items selected by them when they prefer to go for buffet at the table. Given their advanced age they find it difficult to balance the loaded plates, everytime they need refill.

The food is good. But i feel the ambience is not up to the mark. Especially the flooring does not give u a good feel. The service is good. When we visited they had avial which was really good. The atmosphere is quite cozy but for the flooring.
